OLIVER WIND ENERGY CENTER II, LLC
RATE SCHEDULE FERC NO. 1
Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service
Oliver Wind Energy Center II, LLC ("Oliver II") provides Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service ("Reactive Supply Service") from the Oliver II generating facility ("Oliver II Facility").
Oliver II is a wind turbine generating facility located in Oliver County, North Dakota. The Oliver II Facility is interconnected to transmission facilities owned by Allete, Inc., d/b/a Minnesota Power, and under the operational control of the Midcontinent Independent System Operator, Inc. ("MISO").
This Rate Schedule FERC No. 1 sets forth Oliver II's revenue requirement for Reactive Supply Service from the Oliver II Facility. This Rate Schedule shall be effective upon the date authorized by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission.
Oliver II's monthly fixed revenue requirement consists of the charge for the Fixed Capability Component. Payment to Oliver II shall be subject to Schedule 2 of MISO's Open Access Transmission Tariff.
MONTHLY REVENUE REQUIREMENT: The Annual Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $190,000.00. The Monthly Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $15,833.33.
